This paper is about Bayesian deep learning and neural network structures, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on classification and segmentation tasks, which are common in computer vision, suggesting cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses stochastic variational inference techniques, which are commonly used in neural networks and optimization, suggesting cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses uncertainty estimation, which is relevant to control and systems engineering, suggesting cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
